The macro definition itself does not create unreachable code. However, a violation would occur if the constant macro is used in a conditional that makes one branch impossible to execute, e.g.:

if (METAL_IRQ_ENABLE) {
    /* executed */
} else {
    /* unreachable code — violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1 */
}

In the provided function metal_softirq_set_enable(enable is a runtime parameter), using METAL_IRQ_ENABLE (1U) in the comparison does not make either branch unreachable, so no violation here.
